Coinbase’s Layer-2 network Base continues to strengthen its position as a leading Ethereum scaling solution. In March 2026, the team released its official 2026 Mission, Vision, and Strategy, focusing on three key pillars: building global markets, scaling payments with stablecoins, and becoming the top home for builders. 

The roadmap emphasizes tokenized real-world assets (RWAs) such as stocks, commodities, and equities, alongside crypto-native products like perpetual futures and prediction markets. Base aims to capitalize on the massive momentum of stablecoins — having already processed over $17 trillion in volume across 26 currencies and 17 countries in the previous year. 

Technically, Base is reducing reliance on the Optimism OP Stack and transitioning toward its own proprietary infrastructure for greater independence and scalability. The network has shown strong onchain activity, with high daily active addresses and growing DeFi TVL driven by protocols like Aerodrome and Morpho.Additionally, support for AI-driven applications and agent-based economies is gaining traction. With low fees, fast finality, and Coinbase’s distribution power, Base is positioning itself as core infrastructure for the emerging global onchain economy.The ecosystem remains highly active, with ongoing innovation in social apps, DeFi, and tokenized markets making it one of the most developer-friendly chains right now.

